This paper discusses the technical architecture of the National Science, Mathematics, Engineering, and Technology Education Digital Library (NSDL), which is a digital library project funded by the National Science Foundation. The paper covers topics such as library content, library services, metadata, and functional models, which are all relevant to the field of digital libraries (cs.DL). The paper also discusses information retrieval (cs.IR) and metadata, which are important components of digital libraries. Additionally, the paper discusses library services and education (cs.LIB, cs.ET, cs.EDU), which are relevant to the field of library science and education.
